info.description: Description: pyAgrum is a scientific C++ and Python library dedicated to Bayesian Networks and other Probabilistic Graphical Models.  It provides a high-level interface to the part of the C++ aGrUM library allowing to create, model, learn, use, calculate with and embed Bayesian Networks. Some specific (python and C++) codes are added in order to simplify and extend the aGrUM API. The module is mainly generated by the SWIG interface generator.
